               <p>CHARLES M'DONNELL. This coat hung in my hall, <placeName id="t18270531-284-crimeloc1528">No. 8, Thornton-place, Regent's-park</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-284-crimeloc1528" type="placeName" value="No. 8, Thornton-place, Regent's-park"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-284-crimeloc1528" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-284-off1526 t18270531-284-crimeloc1528"></join>, on Saturday the 2d of June, and while I was out I heard it was taken. I went to the office and found it there.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-284-person1555">
                  ANN 
                  SUTTON
               <interp inst="t18270531-284-person1555" type="surname" value="SUTTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-284-person1555" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-284-person1555" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a servant at No. 8, Thornton-place. Mr. McDonnell lodged there. On Saturday last, the prisoner came with a letter, and told me to take it up to mistress. I went up, and when I was on the stairs I heard him come along the hall. I looked down and saw him take this coat off the pegs, he doubled it under his<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182705310108"></xptr>arm and went out - I gave an alarm. Turner stopped him and I took the coat from him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-284-person1556">
                  EDWARD 
                  TURNER
               <interp inst="t18270531-284-person1556" type="surname" value="TURNER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-284-person1556" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-284-person1556" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I stopped the prisoner as he was running - Sutton had taken the coat from him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was in distress and had been drinking.</p>
               <p>
